  "texts": [
    "However, utilizing a crossbar array offers a lightweight approach to executing MAC operations.",
    "In this approach, the weights representing matrix elements are programmed into memristors, while the input vector is converted into voltage signals applied to WLs.",
    "The resulting output currents from BLs represent the MAC result, following the principles of Ohm's law (multiplication) and Kirchhoff's current law (accumulation).",
    "This computation exhibits massive parallelism and high energy efficiency in an ideal scenario.Nevertheless, achieving high accuracy in MAC operations poses challenges due to variations among memristor devices and discrepancies in analog-to-digital conversion.",
    "Therefore, ongoing research efforts are focused on enhancing the accuracy of these operations."
  ],
